SERVICE CLOUD
Display and Edit a Call Center

A call center in Salesforce corresponds to a single computer-telephony integration (CTI) system already in place at your organization. Users must be assigned to a call center record before they can use any Service Cloud Call Center features.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

USER PERMISSIONS
NEEDED
To view or edit a call center: Manage Call Centers

From Setup, enter Call Centers in the Quick Find box, then select Call Centers. Click the name of the call center that you want to view.

From the Call Center Detail page you can:
Click Edit to modify the properties of the call center.
Click Delete to erase the call center record from Salesforce. When you delete a call center, all associated directory numbers are also deleted.
Click Clone to create a duplicate copy of the call center with the same fields and values as the current call center.
Click Manage Call Center Users to designate users as members of this call center.

NOTE Some Service Cloud Call Center features arenâ€™t available with your softphone because of customizations that have been made for your organization. See your administrator for details.
